You have set your home page in ModelAndView object something like this

    @RequestMapping(value = &quot;/&quot;, method = RequestMethod.GET)
    public ModelAndView newStudentForm() {
    
        ModelAndView mav = new ModelAndView(&quot;index&quot;); 
    
        mav.getModelMap().put(&quot;allGroups&quot;, gss.selectAllGroups()); // add all available groups
    
        return mav;
    }

you don&#39;t need to have welcome page as the moment you hit **/** it will call the above method.
delete this code

    &lt;welcome-file-list&gt;
    &lt;welcome-file&gt;/WEB-INF/jsp/index.jsp&lt;/welcome-file&gt;
      &lt;/welcome-file-list&gt;

you have to return the view name in your controller.
since you configured the InternalResourceViewResolver with prefix /WEB-INF/jsp/ and suffix .jsp you should return `index` to get `/WEB-INF/jsp/index.jsp`  as view.

`ModelAndView mav = new ModelAndView(&quot;index&quot;);

You can achieve your workflow as below: 

Basically your web application will look into welcome page and /redirect is fired which is captured by controller and execute the logic to get all available groups from DB and show in the startup page. 

In web.xml add the following code and drop the `startup.jsp` in webapp directory. 

    &lt;welcome-file-list&gt;
        &lt;welcome-file&gt;startup.jsp&lt;/welcome-file&gt;
    &lt;/welcome-file-list&gt;

In `startup.jsp` , add below code:

    &lt;%@ taglib prefix=&quot;c&quot; uri=&quot;http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core&quot; %&gt;
    &lt;html&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;c:redirect url=&quot;/redirect&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;

Finally in the `Controller` , you could add the code below:

    @Controller
    public class HomePageController {
    
        @RequestMapping(value = &quot;/redirect&quot;, method = RequestMethod.GET)
        public String runMethod(HttpServletRequest servletRequest, HttpServletResponse servletResponse) throws IOException {
           // add your logic to fetch all groups 
         return &quot;results&quot;; // return results.jsp where it has all the groups
        }
    }

